# 1. Purpose

The User Interface (UI) System provides players with all gameplay information while keeping the game board as the primary focus.

The UI must communicate game state clearly, minimize distractions, and enable one-handed gameplay on portrait-oriented Android devices.

The UI should never force players to search for important information.

---

# 2. Design Philosophy

Project Velir's UI follows five principles.

### Clarity

Important information should always be visible.

---

### Simplicity

Avoid unnecessary windows and clutter.

---

### Consistency

Buttons, icons, colors, and layouts should behave consistently throughout the game.

---

### Responsiveness

Every player action should receive immediate visual feedback.

---

### Mobile First

Every interface should be designed specifically for portrait smartphones.

---

# 3. UI Architecture

The UI consists of independent modules.

```text id="ui_architecture"
Main UI

↓

Top HUD

↓

Game Board

↓

Bottom Action Panel

↓

Popup Layer

↓

Overlay Layer
```

Each module is responsible for one area of the screen.

