---

# 5. Top HUD

Displays permanent match information.

Contents:

* Active Kingdom
* Round Number
* Turn Number
* Kingdom Banner
* Active Player Indicator

This area remains visible during gameplay.

---

# 6. Resource Panel

Displays the four primary resources.

| Resource  | Icon  | Color  |
| --------- | ----- | ------ |
| Gold      | Coin  | Gold   |
| Army      | Sword | Red    |
| Influence | Lotus | Purple |
| Prestige  | Crown | Blue   |

Values update immediately after every change.

---

# 7. Bottom Action Panel

Contains player actions.

Version 1 buttons:

* Roll Dice
* End Turn
* Menu

Future buttons:

* Recruit
* Trade
* Diplomacy
* Kingdom
* Inventory

Buttons enable and disable automatically depending on game state.

---

# 8. Tile Information Panel

When a tile is selected or landed upon, the panel displays:

* Tile Name
* Tile Type
* Description
* Reward
* Penalty
* Current Owner (if applicable)

The panel automatically closes after movement completes.

---

# 9. Popup Windows

Temporary popups include:

* Event Cards
* Battle Results
* Ancient Discoveries
* Rewards
* Confirmation Dialogs

Popups should interrupt gameplay only when necessary.

---

# 10. Kingdom Information Screen

Displays:

* Kingdom Banner
* Commander
* Passive Ability
* Current Resources
* Statistics
* Controlled Ancient Sites

Accessible from the Pause Menu.

---

# 11. Pause Menu

Contains:

* Resume
* Save Game
* Load Game
* Settings
* Restart Match
* Exit to Main Menu

Gameplay pauses immediately when opened.

---

# 12. Victory Screen

Displays:

* Winning Kingdom
* Final Prestige
* Match Duration
* Resources
* Battle Statistics
* Ancient Discoveries
* Play Again Button
* Main Menu Button

Victory should feel rewarding.

---

# 13. Statistics Screen

Displays:

* Total Turns
* Battles Won
* Battles Lost
* Gold Earned
* Army Recruited
* Influence Gained
* Prestige Earned
* Ancient Sites Controlled

Statistics encourage replayability.

---

# 14. Visual Style

UI should resemble:

* Stone carvings
* Bronze ornaments
* Palm-leaf manuscripts
* Temple engravings

Avoid modern flat-design aesthetics.

The interface should feel handcrafted.

---

# 15. Color System

Primary Colors

| Purpose    | Color      |
| ---------- | ---------- |
| Background | Sandstone  |
| Primary UI | Bronze     |
| Accent     | Royal Gold |
| Positive   | Green      |
| Negative   | Crimson    |
| Neutral    | Granite    |

Kingdom colors override accent colors where appropriate.

---

# 16. Typography

Primary Font

Historical-inspired serif font.

Fallback

Readable sans-serif.

Requirements:

* Large text
* High contrast
* Excellent readability

No decorative fonts during gameplay.

---

# 17. Icons

Every gameplay element has a dedicated icon.

Examples:

* Gold Coin
* Sword
* Crown
* Temple
* Harbor
* Scroll
* Shield
* Dice

Icons should remain recognizable even at small sizes.

---

# 18. Animations

UI animations should remain subtle.

Examples:

* Button Press
* Resource Increase
* Dice Roll
* Popup Fade
* Victory Banner

Target animation duration:

200–500 ms

Players should never wait for UI animations.

---

# 19. Accessibility

Version 1 includes:

* Large touch targets
* Color-blind friendly palette
* Adjustable text size
* High contrast icons

Future versions may add:

* Screen reader support
* Reduced motion mode
* Haptic customization

---

# 20. Runtime UI State

UIManager maintains:

* Active Screen
* Active Popup
* Current HUD
* Selected Tile
* Animation Queue

Only one modal popup may exist at a time.

---

# 21. Signals

UIManager exposes:

* screen_opened
* screen_closed
* popup_opened
* popup_closed
* hud_updated
* button_pressed

Gameplay systems subscribe through signals rather than directly manipulating UI elements.

---

# 22. Performance Requirements

UI Loading

< 500 ms

HUD Update

< 16 ms

Popup Animation

< 500 ms

Target Frame Rate

60 FPS

---

# 23. Testing Checklist

The following tests must pass:

* HUD updates correctly.
* Resource values refresh immediately.
* Popups display correctly.
* Pause Menu functions.
* Victory Screen displays statistics.
* Buttons enable and disable correctly.
* UI scales across supported devices.
* Save/load restores UI state.

---

# 24. Codex Implementation Notes

Create a dedicated **UIManager**.

Responsibilities:

* Manage HUD.
* Manage popups.
* Switch screens.
* Update resources.
* Display notifications.

Individual UI scenes should remain independent.

Avoid direct communication between gameplay systems and UI elements.

All interactions should occur through signals.

---

# 25. Future Expansion

Future UI improvements may include:

* Animated kingdom banners
* Interactive tutorials
* Mini-map
* Gesture navigation
* Theme switching
* Dynamic backgrounds
* Seasonal UI themes
* Tablet-optimized layouts
* Foldable device support

The UI architecture should support these additions without redesigning the existing interface.

---

# 26. Design Principle

The User Interface should become almost invisible.

Players should spend their attention making strategic decisions—not searching menus or interpreting confusing screens.

Every button, panel, and popup should communicate information quickly, elegantly, and consistently.

